Classification of arrows is dependent on the type of Fletch used.  Not necessarily shafts, points, nocks, or combinations of those components.  

The Classifications go as follows:

Class 1 - Round Fletch
Class 2 - Parabolic Fletch
Class 3 - Shield Fletch
Class 4 - Wood Vane Fletch
Class 5 - Bone Vane Fletch
Class 6 - Ceramic Vane Fletch

This classification can be confusing to say the least.  A variety of different arrow combinations can create an arrow of a lower classification having a greater damage or range than a higher classified arrow of different components.

